# Recount — Global Rules

## Stack
- Monorepo: npm workspaces
- API: Node.js 20 + Express 4 (ESM, not CJS)
- Web: Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind
- Extension: Manifest V3, Vanilla JS, no framework
- DB: PostgreSQL via Supabase

## Database
- **Schema reference:** `.cursor/database-schema.md` (tables, columns, RLS, triggers). Update it when migrations change.

## Naming Conventions
- Files: kebab-case (e.g. api-client.js, tab-events.ts)
- React components: PascalCase (e.g. ReportCard.tsx)
- DB tables: snake_case plural (e.g. tab_events)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Environment vars: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Code Style
- ESM imports everywhere (import/export, not require)
- Always use async/await, never raw .then() chains
- All errors must be caught and logged — never swallow silently
- No console.log in production — use a structured logger (pino)
- Never hardcode secrets or API keys
